<number box="[151,165,224,247]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
. Flagellum with an articulated spine-like second flagellomere in addition to a stylus; discal cell open or closed by crossvein m-m; narrow bodied flies 
<emphasis box="[579,1368,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">
........................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[1278,1368,256,279]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Apolysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apolysis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Loew
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,224,439]" box="[151,1435,288,311]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,288,311]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">
- Flagellum without a second flagellomere; discal cell always closed by crossvein m-m; compact bee-like flies ....... 
<number box="[1422,1435,288,311]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="21">
